title: Wildfire in Kelowna, British Columbia, Expected to Leave Lasting Scar
description: Fire is raging in the suburban fringes of the resort town of Kelowna, British Columbia, as a state of emergency across the province continued.

title: Mexico Braces for Rain and Flooding from Hurricane Hilary
description: The torrential rain and flooding that threaten Southern California also menaced Baja California, the western Mexico state that is popular with tourists.

title: Deadly Russian Strike Hits Chernihiv, Ukraine Says
description: The attack, which killed at least seven people and wounded more than 100, came after President Vladimir V. Putin visited a Russian city that was briefly seized by the Wagner group.

title: Egypt’s President Pardons An Arab Spring Activist After Nearly 10 Years in Prison
description: Ahmed Douma was one of the best-known faces of Egypt’s 2011 uprising. Rights groups say thousands of political prisoners remain detained under President Abdel Fattah el-Sisi.

title: Jean-Louis Georgelin, Who Was in Charge of Rebuilding Notre-Dame, Dies
description: A former army chief of staff, he was put in charge of the cathedral’s restoration and prided himself on keeping the project on track.

title: Putin Visits Russian City Seized During Wagner Mutiny
description: President Vladimir V. Putin met with military commanders in Rostov-on-Don in his first publicized trip to the city since an uprising by the Wagner mercenary group in June.

title: U.S.-Japan-South Korea Security Pact Likely to Deepen China’s Dismay
description: What its signers, Japan, South Korea and the United States, call deterrence, China characterizes as encirclement, even provocation.

title: Brazil Found the Last Survivors of an Amazon Tribe. Now What?
description: Pakyi and Tamandua are the final known isolated members of the Piripkura people. They are posing a tricky challenge for Brazil.

title: How European Officials View a Possible Second Trump Term
description: The prospect of a second presidential term for Donald J. Trump has many officials worried about alliance cohesion, NATO and the war in Ukraine.

title: A Ceaseless War Leaves Lethal Threats Lurking Underfoot
description: Even as the fighting in Syria has largely stalled, more than a decade of conflict has left behind an array of unexploded munitions like cluster bombs. An earthquake in February heightened the risks.

title: In France, ‘Climate Fresk’ Global Warming Workshops Are a Hit
description: More than a million people in France have attended a “Climate Fresk” class to understand the process of global warming. The project is now spreading abroad.

title: In China, Artists Create Miniature Homes From Memories
description: China’s rapid economic growth has meant the demolition of countless rural homes, and a burgeoning nostalgia. That’s where the miniaturists come in.

title: Women’s World Cup Final Reminds England of Men’s Team’s Painful History
description: The women play Spain on Sunday, hoping to end a nearly six-decade national wait for a World Cup win — a reminder of the travails of the Three Lions, the country’s long-suffering men’s team.

title: China to Stage Military Exercises Around Taiwan
description: The joint air and sea drills, widely expected in response to a presidential candidate’s visit to the United States, so far appear to be relatively limited.
